As soon as I saw Thaumiel, I was worried. The only Thaumiel-class objects I like are SCP-2000 and SCP-1968, and quite frankly they both stretch the limits.

However, I do feel this uses the Thaumiel very well. It is also an excellent replacement for the old SCP-179.

However, by itself, it has some redeeming qualities, but I also dislike the concept of a benevolent watch god. It feels boring and overly dramatic. No vote for now.

Also, aren't most Thaumiel-class objects hidden, either behind a fake class designation(1968), or a check of some sort(SCP-001-Roget, SCP-2000)? Not that it needs it, but Thaumiel represents a highly classified object, so I feel that lore-wise it should have either a cover story or some kind of credentials check.





